<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="251">
32. - S. - g. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:135461" authority="(Forel) Emery" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Camponotus (Myrmorhachis) hippocrepis Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Myrmorhachis">Myrmorhachis (Forel) Emery</taxonomicName>
emend.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="251">
J'ai fonde le nouveau sous-genre 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:230845" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Camponotus (Myrmacantha)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Myrmacantha">Myrmacantha</taxonomicName>
pour les formes asiatiques et africaines que Forel avait incluses dans ce sous-genre. J'y ai classe en revanche les especes 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:27209" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Camponotus striatus (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatus">C. striatus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:26346" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1870" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Camponotus circularis Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circularis">circularis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:27158" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1887" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Camponotus scissus Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scissus">scissus</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:26417" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Camponotus dimorphus Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimorphus">dimorphus</taxonomicName>
, qui n'etaient, a mon avis, pas bien placees dans les sous-genres 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:183790" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Camponotus (Myrmamblys) Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Myrmamblys">Myrmamblys</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:183776" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Camponotus (Colobopsis) Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Colobopsis">Colobopsis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
